-- North Korea Achieves Nothing Through Provocations, Pentagon Says
-- B y   G o p a l   R a t n a m
-- 2013-03-08T18:34:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-08/north-korea-achieves-nothing-through-provocations-pentagon-says.html
North Korea “will achieve nothing
through threats of provocations,” Pentagon spokesman  George
Little  said today in an e-mailed statement.  Little said the U.S. “is fully capable of defending itself
and our allies” against a North Korean attack and is “firmly
committed to the defense of” South Korea and Japan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gopal Ratnam in Kabul at 
 gratnam1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
